snippet: Iceland’s governing coalition is facing tough competition from parties that are skeptical about joining the European Union.
abstract: Iceland largely suspends talks on joining European Union that began after its banking sector collapsed in 2008; announcement is made by governing coalition, whose members are facing tough competition from parties skeptical about EU membership.
lead_paragraph: Iceland’s governing coalition is facing tough competition from parties that are skeptical about joining the European Union.

headline.seo: Iceland Suspends E.U. Talks Ahead of Elections
headline.main: Iceland Suspends E.U. Talks Ahead of Elections
